Vheadline
p2
VIn his inimitable way
p3
sVnews
p4
VIt was a packed hall at Rasika Ranjana Sabha in Tiruchi when Sikkil Gurucharan gave his mature vocal recital in connection with Professor D.N. Krishnamurthy (popularly known as DNK) memorial concert.From start to finish, this prodigy, from the celebrated Sikkil family kept up the tempo of the concert which was two and a half hour programme.Soul-stirring renditionBeginning with a varnam in Kalyani (&#8216;Vanajakshi'), he amazed the audience with his Saurashtram (&#8216;Ranganathude'). His melismatic Brindavana Saranga (&#8216;Rangapuravihara') with apt swaras and niravals spoke of his scholarship in handling tough components of music and would long be remembered. He took up Varali for ragam, tanam and pallavi and excelled in his performance. His Ragamalika was soul-stirring and was rendered with much felicity bringing out the nuances in each of the ragas.Gurucharan concluded the programme with an evergreen melody, &#8216;Varugalamo' in Manji in his inimitable and mellowing voice. He was accompanied by Ramanujacharyulu on the violin, Palladam Ravi on the mridangam and Tiruchi Murali on the ghatam.N.S. Krishnamachari, one of the old friends of Professor DNK, who spoke on the occasion, said late DNK was a multi-faceted personality. He recalled the yeoman services rendered by DNK for the promotion of music in the state.DNK's son D.K. Narasimhan welcomed the gathering and N. Sekar, secretary of the Rasika Ranjana Sabha proposed a vote of thanks.
